---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Layout title="Privacy Policy - Rex">
  <div class="min-h-screen bg-zinc-950">
    <Header />
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 py-12">
        <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-white mb-8">Privacy Policy</h1>
        <div class="prose prose-invert prose-zinc max-w-none">
          <p class="text-zinc-300 text-lg mb-8">
            Last updated: June 24, 2025
          </p>

          <section class="mb-8">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">1. Information We Collect</h2>

            <h3 class="text-xl font-medium text-white mb-3">Automatically Collected Information</h3>
            <p class="text-zinc-300 mb-4">
              When you visit our documentation website, we may automatically collect:
            </p>
            <ul class="text-zinc-300 mb-4 list-disc pl-6">
              <li>IP address and general location information</li>
              <li>Browser type and version</li>
              <li>Pages visited and time spent on the site</li>
              <li>Referring website information</li>
              <li>Device and screen resolution information</li>
            </ul>

            <h3 class="text-xl font-medium text-white mb-3">Information You Provide</h3>
            <p class="text-zinc-300 mb-4">
              We may collect information you voluntarily provide when you:
            </p>
            <ul class="text-zinc-300 mb-4 list-disc pl-6">
              <li>Contribute to the Rex project on GitHub</li>
              <li>Report issues or participate in discussions</li>
              <li>Contact us directly</li>
            </ul>
          </section>

          <section class="mb-8">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">2. How We Use Information</h2>
            <p class="text-zinc-300 mb-4">
              We use collected information to:
            </p>
            <ul class="text-zinc-300 mb-4 list-disc pl-6">
              <li>Improve the documentation website and user experience</li>
              <li>Understand how the documentation is being used</li>
              <li>Provide technical support and respond to inquiries</li>
              <li>Monitor website performance and security</li>
              <li>Comply with legal obligations</li>
            </ul>
          </section>

          <section class="mb-8">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">3. Third-Party Services</h2>

            <h3 class="text-xl font-medium text-white mb-3">Analytics</h3>
            <p class="text-zinc-300 mb-4">
              We may use analytics services (such as Google Analytics) to understand website usage. These services may collect information about your visits across different websites.
            </p>

            <h3 class="text-xl font-medium text-white mb-3">Hosting and CDN</h3>
            <p class="text-zinc-300 mb-4">
              Our website is hosted on third-party services that may collect standard web server logs and information.
            </p>

            <h3 class="text-xl font-medium text-white mb-3">GitHub</h3>
            <p class="text-zinc-300 mb-4">
              If you interact with our GitHub repository, GitHub's privacy policy applies to that data.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section class="mb-8">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">4. Cookies and Local Storage</h2>
            <p class="text-zinc-300 mb-4">
              Our website may use cookies and local storage to:
            </p>
            <ul class="text-zinc-300 mb-4 list-disc pl-6">
              <li>Remember your preferences (theme, language)</li>
              <li>Improve website functionality</li>
              <li>Provide analytics information</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="text-zinc-300 mb-4">
              You can disable cookies in your browser settings, though this may affect website functionality.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section class="mb-8">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">5. Data Sharing and Disclosure</h2>
            <p class="text-zinc-300 mb-4">
              We do not sell, trade, or otherwise transfer your personal information to third parties, except:
            </p>
            <ul class="text-zinc-300 mb-4 list-disc pl-6">
              <li>To third-party service providers who assist in operating our website</li>
              <li>When required by law or to protect our rights</li>
              <li>In connection with a business transfer or merger</li>
            </ul>
          </section>

          <section class="mb-8">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">6. Data Security</h2>
            <p class="text-zinc-300 mb-4">
              We implement appropriate security measures to protect your information. However, no method of transmission over the internet is 100% secure.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section class="mb-8">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">7. Data Retention</h2>
            <p class="text-zinc-300 mb-4">
              We retain information only as long as necessary for the purposes outlined in this policy or as required by law.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section class="mb-8">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">8. Your Rights</h2>
            <p class="text-zinc-300 mb-4">
              Depending on your location, you may have rights regarding your personal information, including:
            </p>
            <ul class="text-zinc-300 mb-4 list-disc pl-6">
              <li>Access to your personal information</li>
              <li>Correction of inaccurate information</li>
              <li>Deletion of your information</li>
              <li>Objection to processing</li>
              <li>Data portability</li>
            </ul>
          </section>

          <section class="mb-8">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">9. Children's Privacy</h2>
            <p class="text-zinc-300 mb-4">
              Our website is not directed to children under 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section class="mb-8">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">10. International Data Transfers</h2>
            <p class="text-zinc-300 mb-4">
              Your information may be transferred to and processed in countries other than your own. We ensure appropriate safeguards are in place for such transfers.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section class="mb-8">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">11. Changes to This Policy</h2>
            <p class="text-zinc-300 mb-4">
              We may update this privacy policy from time to time. Changes will be posted on this page with an updated revision date.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section class="mb-8">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">12. Contact Us</h2>
            <p class="text-zinc-300 mb-4">
              If you have questions about this privacy policy or our privacy practices, please contact us:
            </p>
            <ul class="text-zinc-300 mb-4 list-disc pl-6">
              <li>GitHub: <a href="https://github.com/OMouta/Rex" class="text-primary-400 hover:text-primary-300 underline">OMouta/Rex</a></li>
              <li>Email: contact@moutaz.lol</li>
            </ul>
          </section>

          <section class="mb-8">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">13. Framework Usage</h2>
            <p class="text-zinc-300 mb-4">
              <strong>Important:</strong> This privacy policy covers the Rex documentation website only. When you use the Rex framework in your own projects, you are responsible for implementing your own privacy policy and data handling practices for your applications.
            </p>
          </section>
        </div>
    </div>
    <Footer />
  </div>
</Layout>
